
[1]fabric

   FABRIC, n. [L., a frame, a workman.]

   1. The structure of any thing; the manner in which the parts of a thing
   are untied by art and labor; workmanship; texture. This is cloth of a
   beautiful fabric.

   2. The frame or structure of a building; construction. More generally,
   the building itself; an edifice; a house; a temple; a church; a bridge,
   &c. The word is usually applied to a large building.

   3. Any system composed of connected parts; as the fabric of the
   universe.

   4. Cloth manufactured.

   Silks and other fine fabrics of the east.

        FABRIC, v.t To frame; to build; to construct. [Little used.]
